  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: When a user has message content in the message input box and taps on the chat screen area, - we hide the keyboard. However, along with that, we clear the message content which is entered. We need to keep it.\r\n**Note:** If user taps on back to Home screen button (`<` one) or chat settings (`...` one) in the app top bar - keyboard hides but message input box content is not cleared after the user returns back to chat screen, as expected.  \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nMessage content is kept in message input box after a tap on chat view screen\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nMessage content cleared from message input box after a tap on chat view screen\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Start any type of a new chat (e.g. join public chat `tappingoutside`)\r\n- Tap inside message input box\r\n- Type a text (any text with/without emoji)\r\n- Tap inside chat view above message input box\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 333rd nightly develop, release 0.9.15\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\nTF video with the issue: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8073365/sessions/21/?accessToken=XDtUp-4DWxbJKB92KwMtPA0DwBU",
